<p>This web page describes resources, related to Bulgarian projects for
   creating, supporting and improving free software and documentation. In
   general, these projects are efforts of the whole <a 
   href="http://fsa-bg.org/bg/members">Bulgarian free software community</a>
   to translate and adopt free software and documentation in Bulgarian language.
   If you wish to help us, please don't hesitate to contact with the relevant
   coordinators. For instance, if you wish to contribute to <a href="$(HOME)">\
   Debian</a>, but you have no programming skills, you can still help with
   translating <a href="$(DEVEL)/website/translating">Debian web pages</a> 
   in your natural language. If you have good knowledge (technical is not 
   necessary, but useful) of English language and wish to see these pages in
   Bulgarian, please contact with the coordinator of Debian Bulgarian
   Translation Project &mdash; <a href="mailto:manitu@fsa-bg.org">Rumen 
   Krasstev</a>.
</p>

<p><em>Many of listed projects below are contributed and supported by members
   of</em> <a href="http://fsa-bg.org/en/what"><strong><q>Free Software 
   Association &mdash; Bulgaria</q></strong></a>.
</p>

<p>Debian specific resources:
</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Debian book in Bulgarian</strong> &mdash;
       <a href="http://debian-book-bg.openfmi.net">http://debian-book-bg.openfmi.net</a>.</li>
<li>Debian Bulgarian users mailing list (recommended encoding &mdash; utf8 or cp1251) &mdash;
       <a href="debian@lists.uni-sofia.bg">debian@lists.uni-sofia.bg</a>.</li>
</ul>

<p>Resources for translators:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Most important mailing list for discussions and information of free 
      software and documentation translations in Bulgarian language &mdash; <a
      href="http://debian.fmi.uni-sofia.bg/mailman/listinfo/ls-dict">LS-Dict
      mailing list</a>.</li>
  <li>Very useful information for translators &mdash; dictionaries, mailing 
      lists, etc:
      <a href="http://fsa-bg.org/bin/view.cgi/Fsasite/InfoTranslators">\
      Translating free software in Bulgarian language</a>.</li>
</ul>

<p>Other Bulgarian translation projects of free software and documentation:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://gnome.cult.bg">Gnome Bulgarian Translation Project</a>.</li>
  <li><a href="http://kde.fsa-bg.org">KDE Bulgarian Translation Project</a>.</li>
  <li><a href="http://bgoffice.sourceforge.net">BG Office Project</a>. Spell
      checker, thesaurus, hyphenation and other tools for OpenOffice, aspell,
      ispell, Mozilla and others.</li>
   <li><a href="http://bg.openoffice.org">OpenOffice for bulgarians project</a>.</li>
</ul>

<p>General Linux specific resources:
</p>
<ul>
   <li>Most visited and well known Bulgarian Linux portal:
       <a href="http://linux-bg.org/"><strong>Linux for bulgarians</strong></a>.</li>
   <li>Linux Bulgarian users mailing list (recommended encoding &mdash; utf8):
       <a href="http://www.linux-bulgaria.org/public/mail_list.html">\
       lug-bg@linux-bulgaria.org</a>. Supported by the <q>Linux-Bulgaria.org</q>
       <a href="http://debian.gabrovo.com/">web site</a>.</li>
</ul>
